{"type":"message","id":"b5ff4a27","parentId":"5d4116e4","timestamp":"2026-05-09T14:21:07.277Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if they can put all their stuff in a big folder in Dropbox (since free Dropbox storage is limited). They seem to be asking if they can skip the symlink approach and just use Dropbox as the main storage location.\n\nThey want to put everything in one big Dropbox folder rather than a specific .openclaw folder in their home directory. This makes sense since the free Dropbox storage isn't huge.\n\nLet me think about this - yes, they can do this. Instead of having ~/.openclaw as a symlink to Dropbox, they can:\n1. Have the workspace in Dropbox (e.g., Dropbox/workspace)\n2. Use openclaw workspace command to set the workspace path, OR\n3. Create a symlink\n\nActually, let me think about the cleanest approach:\n\n\n- Set the workspace path in openclaw config to point to the Dropbox location instead of using symlinks\n- This is cleaner than trying to redirect the entire ~/.openclaw directory, which could cause issues with other config files\n- The workspace setting would handle the files that actually need syncing (SOUL, IDENTITY, MEMORY, etc.)\n","thinkingSignature":"d63d1bfcf4aba3bbb796985f65e06206850e68bf2ea19854a1c8e944615e3c64"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nได้เลยครับ! ถ้า Dropbox ฟรีพื้นที่น้อย ก็แค่เปลี่ยน **workspace path** ใน config ไปชี้ที่ Dropbox เลย ไม่ต้องย้ายทั้ง .openclaw folder\n\n### วิธี:\n1. สร้าง folder `Dropbox/owen-workspace/`\n2. เปลี่ยน workspace path ใน config ให้ชี้ไปที่นั่นแทน `~/.openclaw/workspace`\n\n```bash\n# บน Windows\nopenclaw config set workspace.path \"C:\\Users\\Apinan\\Dropbox\\owen-workspace\"\n\n# บน MacBook  \nopenclaw config set workspace.path \"/Users/apinan/Dropbox/owen-workspace\"\n```\n\n### สิ่งที่อยู่ใน owen-workspace:\n- SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md, MEMORY.md, AGENTS.md\n- HEARTBEAT.md, pending-tasks.md\n- skills, memory, อื่นๆ\n\n### สิ่งที่อยู่ใน ~/