{"type":"message","id":"863ea657","parentId":"c241b773","timestamp":"2026-05-09T14:34:58.437Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze what happened:\n\n1. At 21:15:41, the system tried to stop hermes-gateway (via `systemctl --user stop hermes-gateway`)\n2. At 21:18:11 (about 2.5 minutes later), systemd hit its timeout and started killing all processes with SIGKILL\n3. The main process (python, PID 3102107) was killed with SIGKILL\n4. All the child processes (MCP servers) were also killed\n\nThe root cause: Someone or something triggered a stop (`systemctl --user stop hermes-gateway`), but the service didn't respond to SIGTERM within the timeout period, so systemd force-killed it with SIGKILL.\n\nLet me look at the logs before the stop to see if there was any warning or error that preceded the stop.\n\nKey observation:\n- 1.7G memory peak is high\n- The stop was triggered by something at 21:15 - there was a bash command running `systemctl --user stop hermes-gateway`\n\nLet me check if there were any OOM or memory issues before the stop.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_m2ywqz0g","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"journalctl --user -u hermes-gateway.service --since \"1 hour ago\" --no-pager 2>&1 | grep -i \"error\\|error\\|fail\\|oom\\|killed\\|memory\\|crash\\|exception\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778337283908,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778337292953"}}
