{"type":"message","id":"c5bfc469","parentId":"f88ae836","timestamp":"2026-05-09T14:35:14.620Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me think about what happened:\n\n1. There was a warning at 20:50 - \"Failed to generate context summary: 404 page not found\" - this is likely from OpenClaw's model provider\n2. Around 21:11, multiple sudo authentication failures occurred\n3. At 21:15, something triggered a stop of hermes-gateway\n4. The stop didn't complete gracefully, so systemd force-killed all processes with SIGKILL at 21:18\n\nThe key question is: what triggered the stop? Let me check if it was an automatic restart or something else.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the logs, I see the systemctl stop was triggered by a bash command that ran at 21:15:41. This is likely part of Hermes' own restart mechanism (the Hermes agent itself may have tried to restart the gateway).\n\nLet me also check for any memory issues or if the process was stuck.\n\nThe main issue seems to be:\n1. Hermes gateway had many child processes (at least 30+ processes)\n2. When it received the stop signal, it didn't gracefully shut down within systemd's timeout\n3. Systemd killed it\n\nThis is likely just a normal restart that went wrong because too many child processes didn't clean up properly.\n\nLet me restart the service and see if it comes back.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"สาเหตุ: Hermes ถูกสั่ง `stop` แล้วมัน **shutdown ไม่ทัน** — systemd เลยยิง SIGKILL เพราะ timeout ครับ\n\nไม่มี error ร้ายแรงก่อนหน้า มีแค่:\n- `context summary` ฟ้อง 404 (ไม่สำคัญ)\n- มี sudo auth fail หลายครั้งที่ 21:11\n\nสรุป: เหมือนมันโดน restart แล้ว shutdown ตัวเองไม่ทัน เพราะมี child process เยอะเกิน (MCP servers 30+ ตัว)\n\nจะให้ผม **start กลับ** เลยไหมครับ? 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"deepseek-v4-pro:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"ou