{"type":"message","id":"851a3597","parentId":"7c8dcf24","timestamp":"2026-05-09T15:25:04.497Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"มึงส่งมาเนี่ยเป็นเสียงภาษาอังกฤษ\" meaning \"You sent this and it's English voice\" - so the TTS message I supposedly sent was in English. But the reply target shows my message was in Thai text... So it seems like maybe the TTS was actually sending audio but in English? Wait, but I haven't been sending any TTS at all.\n\nWait - let me re-read. The user sent a voice message (file_18 which is an mp3) along with the text \"มึงส่งมาเนี่ยเป็นเสียงภาษาอังกฤษ\" = \"you sent this and it's English audio\"\n\nLooking at the reply context, it shows that my (Owen_bot) message that was replied to was:\n\"ผล:\\n\\nอย่างที่มึงส่งมา...\"\n\nSo my text reply was in Thai. But the user is saying there was an English audio message that came with it. This is confusing because I haven't been sending any TTS.\n\nWait - I think what's happening is that OpenClaw's TTS auto-reply is generating English audio for my Thai text responses. That would be the issue! The user has `messages.tts.auto: \"always\"` set, so every text reply is being converted to speech. But the TTS provider (Microsoft Edge) might be reading the English model and generating English audio even when the text is in Thai.\n\nActually no, the user's message says \"มึงส่งมาเนี่ยเป็นเสียงภาษาอังกฤษ\" = \"you sent this and it's English audio\". So they received an English audio message from me. But I haven't been sending audio. The auto TTS feature might be converting my text to speech, but the Microsoft Edge TTS is producing English audio when fed Thai text.\n \nSo the auto TTS is working but producing English audio instead of Thai when converting my Thai text. The user is hearing an English voice message accompanying my text reply, which means the TTS system is generating audio in the wrong language. I need to check what TTS configuration is actually being used, since setting Microsoft as the provider should theoretically support Thai.\n","thinkingSignature":"ebcf5ddbd23e74fae8619a47450cb87b5069926eca63ad24022ffda0ada1f5a3"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\nเดี๋ยวผมเช็ค audio นี้ก่อนครับ 🧑🏼‍💻\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3hkl0ubrhyly_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ffmpeg -i \"/home/apinan/.openclaw/media/inbound/file_18---908731d6-07a6-45dd-a25a-d912fb3acbf9.mp3\" -ar 16000 -ac 1 \"/tmp/audio_msg11.wav\" -y 2>&1 | tail -2"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1993,"output":647,"cacheRead":55488,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58128,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778340285720,"responseId":"064e84c019025febc6c35b2956e331a1"}}
