{"type":"message","id":"a79ce452","parentId":"08b3c846","timestamp":"2026-05-09T15:26:12.493Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user sent me a voice message where they're saying the TTS voice message I supposedly sent them is in English. They're saying something like \"TTS face with open mouth, TTS text, voice message, Hermes, OpenClaw, adult medium light skin tone, emoji modifier, laptop computer.\"\n\nWait - I think they're describing what the English TTS is saying. So the TTS from OpenClaw/Hermes is indeed outputting English audio when it should be outputting Thai.\n\nSo the issue is that when I set `messages.tts.auto: always` and `messages.tts.provider: microsoft`, and the gateway restarts, somehow the TTS is being triggered but it's speaking English instead of Thai.\n\n\nI need to figure out how to make the Microsoft TTS produce Thai output instead - either through a language code parameter in the config or by switching to a different TTS engine that supports Thai. I'm not entirely sure what the Thai phrase was, but the user is clearly frustrated that I've set up TTS without properly configuring the language to match their needs. They're demonstrating that the current setup is broken by playing back what the English TTS is producing. I should disable TTS for now and figure out how to properly configure the language setting before enabling it again.","thinkingSignature":"774c982ae9824e7301369c80fdf6b4d82bd69de281c8566025683676b6fb9d58"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nเข้าใจแล้วครับ 😮 ตอนนี้ TTS มันส่งเป็นภาษาอังกฤษจริงๆ ใช่ไหม — ผมฟังออกว่า:\n\n> \"TTS face with open mouth, TTS text, voice message, Hermes, OpenClaw, adult medium light skin tone, emoji modifier, laptop computer\"\n\nนี่คือสิ่งที่ TTS Microsoft พูดออกมา 😱\n\nขอโทษครับเจ้านาย — ผมตั้งค่า TTS แล้วมัน auto reply เป็นเสียงอังกฤษไป ทั้งที่เจ้านายต้องการไทย\n\nผม **ปิด TTS auto** ก่อนเลยนะครับ:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8qr4lkj7yivb_1","name":"exec