{"type":"message","id":"67661535","parentId":"697ebfa1","timestamp":"2026-05-09T15:42:00.207Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user's audio was sent twice (duplicate). The transcription shows \"I am.\" which seems like English audio that was sent twice. This might be the same English TTS that was auto-sent before. Let me check if there are any pending audio files.\n\nActually wait - this audio is 0.65 seconds and says \"I am.\" in English. This looks like it's a response from the auto-TTS that was sending English audio. The user might be sending this back to me to show what was sent.\n\nBut wait, looking at the conversation flow - the user is sending voice messages to me, not receiving them. The \"I am.\" could be the user (or someone else?) saying \"I am\" or it could be TTS response from another session.\n\n\nThe timing and source are unclear - the audio could be from the user or another system like Hermes sending back an automatic TTS response. I should ask the user what this is about since I'm not certain whether they sent it to show me the auto-TTS problem or if there's something else happening.","thinkingSignature":"88c383f2c35e1cfe7381e0aac5e9a05a8d274f9890e8761591bd18ea707a682a"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n**ผล:**\n\n> I am.\n\nนี่เป็น **ภาษาอังกฤษ** อีกแล้วครับ — 0.65 วินาที ฟังเหมือน auto-TTS ที่ยังส่ง English ออกไป\n\nเจ้านายกดส่งไฟล์นี้มาเองใช่ไหมครับ หรือได้รับจาก Hermes ตอบกลับมา? 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":119,"output":371,"cacheRead":61536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62026,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778341299715,"responseId":"064e88b560d5b0fc9c0b7ee7157b2502"}}
