{"type":"message","id":"e4c4855f","parentId":"0858a53c","timestamp":"2026-05-09T15:46:27.985Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I just created the skill file. But wait, the user's request is more nuanced. Let me re-read what they wanted:\n\n\"ตั้ง skill /เสียงพูด ถ้ากดเปิด skillนี้ให้โหลดเข้ามาเลย\"\n\nThey want to set up a skill called \"/เสียงพูด\" - when they activate the skill, it should load/preload the whisper model into memory. They want the model preloaded so it doesn't take 10-20 seconds each time.\n\nBut skill files in OpenClaw don't really work like \"load-on-demand\" preloading in the traditional sense. Skill files are more like documentation/instructions for the agent. The actual preloading would need to happen via a background process or cron job.\n\n\nThe actual preloading logic would need to be implemented separately, maybe through a background task or startup script rather than through the skill file itself. files define WHAT to do, not HOW to preload a model into memory permanently.\n\nLet me re-read the user's request again: \"ตั้ง skill /เสียงพูด ถ้ากดเปิด skillนี้ให้โหลดเข้ามาเลย\"\n\nI think the user wants a slash command `/เสียงพูด` that, when triggered, preloads the whisper model. They want it so that when they enable the skill, the model gets loaded into memory right away.\n\nFor OpenClaw skills with slash commands, I need to check if that's even possible. Looking at the system, skill files describe how to handle certain situations but there's no standard slash command registration mechanism. I'd need to check the skill-creator skill to understand how to set this up properly.\n\nActually, thinking about this differently - the skill I've created serves as documentation so I'll remember to use `large-v3` and keep the model preloaded. The user probably means they want the model preloaded when the skill loads, but I should probably just create the skill file for now and explain that preloading would require a background process. I should focus on creating the skill documentation first, then suggest preloading the model as a background process to keep it in memory between requests.","thinkingSignature":"9769a0b19207387cd8425db971af2a70a7b82901a37aaedd36c63fb6f10eab0b"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nสร้าง skill แล้วครับ ✅ อยู่ที่ `~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/เสียงพูด/SKILL.md`\n\nแต่ skill เป็นแค่เอกสารบอกผมว่าจะใช้ model ไหน ถ้าเจ้านายอยากให้ **โหลด model ค้างไว้ใน memory ไม่ต้องรอโหลดใหม่ทุกครั้ง** — ผมต้องเขียน script preload รัน background ไว้ตลอด\n\nจะให้ทำแบบนั้นไหมครับ? 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":719,"output":683,"cacheRead":63744,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65146,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778341567995,"responseId":"064e89c1b8546c35be07fa07db920915"}}
