{"type":"message","id":"6cf0d7c2","parentId":"91930524","timestamp":"2026-05-09T16:06:19.190Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The boss said \"ที่กูรอนั้นแล้ว\" - meaning \"that's what I was waiting for\" or \"that's the one I was waiting for\". So the boss seems to be confirming something, maybe responding to the TTS Thai voice test I was supposed to send but didn't actually send yet.\n\nWait, the boss is listening to something and saying \"ที่กูรอนั้นแล้ว\" - \"that's what I was waiting for\". This sounds like the boss heard the TTS Thai voice that was supposed to be sent. But I don't think I actually sent a TTS voice message yet...\n\nOh wait, maybe OpenClaw did send a TTS voice automatically when I set the TTS to auto. Let me check.\n\nActually the message says the boss received something and is saying \"ที่กูรอนั้นแล้ว\" - \"that's what I was waiting for\". \n\nThe voice message that came through sounds like it could be the TTS test from earlier. Though I'm not entirely certain if the automatic TTS actually fired after the gateway restart, or if this was something else entirely.\n\nBut wait - I set TTS to auto:off earlier, so it shouldn't have been sending anything automatically. Unless the gateway restart triggered something, or maybe I misread what was configured. Let me just focus on the fact that the boss confirmed something came through by saying \"that's what I was waiting for,\" and respond accordingly.\n","thinkingSignature":"4e0fbb4dbf8a32bc1330008690dca86540df44499a28c31471d6c31a0f2ead36"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n**ผล:**\n\n> ที่กูรอนั้นแล้ว\n\nเสียงที่เจ้านายได้ยินมาจากไหนครับ? มาจาก TTS auto ที่ผมตั้งไว้หรือเปล่า? หรือเป็นเสียงอื่น? 🧑🏼‍💻"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":124,"output":425,"cacheRead":72832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":73381,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":177834276